{
  "id": "indus_phase10_ctt_anchored_sa",
  "name": "Indus Phase-10 — CTT-anchored SA + Holdout Recall",
  "description": "Phase-10 H17.7-compliant decipherment graph. Pulls the ICIT corpus, derives per-sign 6-bit role masks (suffix/determinative/numeral/phonetic/logogram/compound) from positional and bigram statistics, then runs simulated-annealing decipherment with the Constraint Topology Theory (Layer1Labs Silicon, 2026) admissibility oracle filtering every proposal step against three competing language models in parallel: Old Tamil (DEDR), Hieroglyphic Luwian, and Mycenaean Greek. The corpus is split 70/30 train/test; SA is fit on the 70% train portion, then evaluated by Holdout Word Recall against attested vocabulary on the 30% held-out partition. Compound bigram dependencies (Cotterell/Eisner 2015 dual-decomposition idea) are scored separately to capture cross-sign coupling that pure CTT (independent constraints) cannot. The DefaultIndusValueRoleMap node feeds the value-role lookup that the CTT oracle uses to forbid (sign, value) pairs whose roles disagree.",
  "auto_migrated": true,
